    "milb_keepers": "Minor-league keepers (max 4 per team). Separate from MLB-level keepers.",
    "rookies": "Legacy duplicate of milb_keepers \u2014 retained for existing code paths; should be merged into milb_keepers in a follow-up.",
    "mulligan2026": "Per LEAGUE_RULES.md: each team has ONE 2026-only mulligan that lets them keep a player whose natural advancement would put them at or below R0 (permanently ineligible). The mulligan-kept player is assigned to R1. If a team uses theirs, add `\"mulligan2026\": true` to the relevant keeper entry in `keepers.{owner}`. Most R1-R4 keepers are NOT mulligans \u2014 they're standard final-year keepers (R5 \u2192 R1, R6 \u2192 R2, etc.); only flag the ones the commissioner explicitly designates as mulligan uses."
